{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, while 61.23% of participants said they value nutritional value, only 30.62%",
    "regularly choose healthy foods.",
    "The interviews explained that this phenomenon of \"different knowledge\" is closely related to factors such as time pressure, emotional feeding, and the scarcity of health options, which corresponds to the ideas of the theory of planned behaviour.",
    "In summary, quantitative data describe trends, while qualitative data provide explanations.",
    "This chapter consolidates research evidence in response to the research questions and literature."
  ]
}